### Docker image archive creation

1) Go to an example shuttle project and build it. Copy the built binary to `deployer/src/builder`.

2) Change directory to `docker/src/builder` and run: 
```bash
mv <project_binary> shuttle-service
```

3) Run:
```bash
docker build . -t shuttle-service -f Containerfile
```

4) Run:
```bash
docker save shuttle-service > shuttle-service.tar
```

5) Optionally, you can remove the shuttle-service docker image:
```bash
docker rmi shuttle-service
```

6) Start the deployer using the `shuttle-service` archive as a parameter for the
`--image-archive-path` flag.